cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.SE 

This paper introduces a new programming language, ProbZelus, which extends an existing synchronous programming language, Zelus, to support probabilistic programming. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. 

Firstly, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a likely category, as the paper introduces a new programming language and discusses its semantics and compilation. 

Secondly, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category, as the paper introduces a probabilistic programming language and discusses inference algorithms for inferring latent model parameters from data. 

Thirdly, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category, as the paper discusses probabilistic modeling and inference, which are key concepts in machine learning. 

Fourthly, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category, as the paper discusses the use of synchronous programming languages for designing and implementing real-time control software. 

Finally, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category, as the paper discusses the design and implementation of a new programming language and its compilation strategy.
